<br>
Llyr (still awed by the visuals) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#767676><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub70.ezboard.com/utenynspiritwolf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tenyn Spiritwolf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#B30000>(12/19/01 11:11:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/fdraconisrampantfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=97.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: LotR (no spoilers)</span><hr size=1> I agree, I saw it this morning and thoroughly enjoyed it.<br>
<br>
Highly recommended.<br>
<br>
Go see it.<br>
<br>
Really.<br>
<br>
Tenyn Spiritwolf<br>
Druid of 20 Circles <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#a8a8a8><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub70.ezboard.com/udruenor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Druenor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 45<br> <font color=#B30000>(12/19/01 11:19:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/fdraconisrampantfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=97.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: LotR (no spoilers)</span><hr size=1> Pure sensory candy.  You will be going back to see it again, just to take in the breathtaking scenes and see what you missed.  Also true to the story; unless you were following along with a book in the theatre you will not find an incredible amount lacking.  And silence!  I do not know about you, but I can't remember the last time I saw a movie hush a crowd. And I am talking about a packed stadium theatre (I can't believe there were that many people there on a Wednesday!) It was epic, but not the kind of epic like the old days of Hollywood. I mean, there were sweeping scenes where thousands of extras and digitally added characters invaded a landscape, but it never seemed to diminish from the actions of the Quest of the Nine.<br>
<br>
An Excited and Utterly Satisfied Moviegoer   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#767676><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub70.ezboard.com/umicenous.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MICENOUS</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 18<br> <font color=#B30000>(12/20/01 8:10:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/fdraconisrampantfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=97.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: LotR (no spoilers)</span><hr size=1> Watched it last night, and I agree.  One of the best booktofilm movies I have seen.  Very close to the Book and I am amazed.  I have long been a Tolkien Fan, and though I feel now that LotR is not the best fantasy book, it is the one that started me into reading fantasy.  I am just really pleased that they(hollywood) did a good job to honor Tolkien and not trash the original idea like so many other booktofilm movies.  Excellent, must see film...which I also found out this morning that the second should be releasing in august 2002..all 3 are already made, but they are releasing them 6mo to a year apart...which is better than having to wait 2 yrs between each film.<br>
<br>
Micenous <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#a8a8a8><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub70.ezboard.com/utenynspiritwolf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tenyn Spiritwolf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#B30000>(12/20/01 8:45:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/fdraconisrampantfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=97.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: LotR (no spoilers)</span><hr size=1> August would be most welcome, tho I had heard (and assumed as much from the trailers) that they were to be released at Christmas time each year (2001-Fellowship, 2002-Two towers, 2003-Return of the King).<br>
<br>
Anyone else hear different?<br>
<br>
Tenyn Spiritwolf<br>
Druid of 20 Circles <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#767676><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub70.ezboard.com/uandrocet.showPublicProfile?language=EN>androcet</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 61<br> <font color=#B30000>(12/20/01 10:00:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/fdraconisrampantfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=97.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.draconisrampant.org/images/Characters/Androcet60.bmp WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: LotR (no spoilers)</span><hr size=1> This was the most awsome visual  spectacle I have ever witnessed.  I saw it in an IMAX theatre and the crowd was totally silent, like stated earlier.  The only time there was any sound was an occasional round of applause or maybe an emotional shout (very appropriate given the scope of this film) after a particularly action-packed scene..(I won't elaborate as to ruin any of the film for anyone who hasn't seen it yet)..  I MUST SEE IT AGAIN WHILE STILL IN THEATRE!!!!!   So should you.<br>
